author: Ari Wasserman, Northeast Ohio Media Group
title: Live score updates and chat: Ohio State football vs. Maryland
text:
COLUMBUS, Ohio -- The top-ranked Ohio State football team is 5-0 but looking to look crisper offensively today as it takes on Maryland in a Big Ten game. The noon kickoff is being shown on the Big Ten Network. The Buckeyes (5-0, 1-0 Big Ten) turned the ball over three times in last Saturday's win at Indiana. Maryland (2-3, 0-1) has been outscored by a combined 73-6 in its last two games.
Join the live chat in the comments below with Northeast Ohio Media Group's coverage team of Doug Lesmerises, Ari Wasserman and Bill Landis, and Plain Dealer columnist Bill Livingston. And click here to view this post on a mobile device.
Second-quarter update: Ohio State and Maryland are tied at 7 after the first quarter. The Buckeyes' lone touchdown came on a three-yard touchdown run from J.T. Barrett, who has seemingly taken over as the Buckeyes' red zone quarterback.
